lenders.name: Winnie
lenders.loan_because:
Born in 1908, Winnie grew up in rural Ontario and Saskatchewan as the daughter of a farming family.  Having lived through hard times, she knew the work required to earn a dollar.  Winnie worked the family farm and cared for her aging parents as her siblings attended school and took careers.

When she passed away in 2010, she left money to those close to her.  I had been troubled to find a way to best put at least some of the money left to me to good use, when I was introduced to Kiva by one of the most incredible people I have ever met -- a selfless, giving young woman with a heart of gold.  It seemed like a natural fit: I could help others who shared Winnie's determined work ethic, and pass along some of her success in the hopes that those who share her spirit and fortitude may attain similar achievements.

Perhaps someone, somewhere, will benefit from Winnie's money as much as I benefited from the years I had her as a close friend, teacher, and mentor.
